metadata.name: For Better Dreams #10
metadata.description:
A radiant talisman. Watchful third eye. Use as directed.

Once minted your patterns maintain their design while stretching to accommodate changes in canvas size.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone. That aside, there are 6 possible color palettes and 7 possible background colors. 

This artwork was created using p5js and utilizes the p5.pattern library created by Taichi Sayama.

metadata.name: Shapes on a Plane #8
metadata.description:
“Shapes on a Plane” explores imaginary structures and worlds through simple shapes. It’s intended for small-scale print.

As a kid I was obsessed with Lego, Duplo, wooden building blocks... anything I could make something with.

I’d spend hours building things, imagining new worlds, new machines, new concepts, then i’d take them apart and create a whole new idea to explore.

To me, this piece to me is a reminder of that time - many days spent exploring ideas with those simple objects - no care for viability, for marketability, for audiences or business. Just pure fun.

Without this time in my life, I doubt I’d have found my passion for creating in the way I do today.

metadata.name: Precision: angles #12
metadata.description:
This is the first hash-derived entry into my "Precisions" series.  I have been using Precisions as a meditative art practice where I focus on exact positioning of elements, less-emphasized colors, and repetition of geometric shapes.  

In "angles", each element is comprised of right triangles transformed over a common point.  I decided to bring some of the fragmentation from my previous project, "Restrictions", to produce irregular works.  I found beauty in that unpredictable asymmetry and feel it really enhances the structure of this piece.

metadata.name: Touch Glass #83
metadata.description:
Touch Glass is an artistic interpretation of the phrase "touch grass", commonly used to express the need to step away from the digital world and reconnect with the physical one. The piece features interactive glass sculptures inspired by the vibrant flora of Finnish summers.

The artwork emerges from an internal dialogue about balancing the life of a generative artist with that of an outdoorsy person who finds peace in foraging for berries and mushrooms in the forests. The tension between these two opposing aspects of life—each both inspiring and hindering the other—reflects a conflict familiar to many. The project seeks to reconcile these elements into a poetic and satisfying experience.

Touch Glass uses hand tracking technology to allow viewers to interact with the artwork, turning the concept of "touching" into a literal, though non-tactile, experience. This form of interaction highlights a sensory aspect often missing in digital environments, reinforcing the need to "touch grass" and reconnect with the physical world.

----------

Controls

[ f ] - fullscreen
[ r ] - refresh with new hash
[ double-click or g ] - toggle settings panel
[ &gallery=60 ] - url parameter for gallery mode that accepts an integer between 10 and 3600 seconds

----------

Display Notes

- Scales to any aspect ratio, but optimized for 16:9, 1:1, and 9:16
- The graphics animate automatically but are interactive with cursor, touch, and hand tracking
- To enable hand tracking, open the settings panel and hover over text to see tooltips
- Touch Glass has been tested on a variety of devices but is optimized for Chrome on desktops
- For performance reasons, hand tracking uses MediaStreamTrackProcessor and OffscreenCanvas, which might not be supported by some devices

----------

Part of Responsive Dreams 2024 Festival
5/6/7 September 2024
Nau Dents de Serra, Roca Umbert Fàbrica de les Arts, Granollers, Barcelona
More info: responsivedreams.com

metadata.name: (un)existing #259
metadata.description:
The existing nature grows on the unexisting spirits.

Generative sketch, based on the pen and ink drawings of Po Sheng Chen. Po Sheng Chen is an Architect who has drawn nothing but Architecture for over 25 years. He tried to explore something different from his previous style (Brutalism with Magical Realism), so developed his own Minimalist Architecture process and style. After breaking up all the complicated elements and symbols, he chose a simple and naive way to present “pure volumes in the space (the essential of Architecture)”: the Use of different densities of vertical lines to create different faces of volumes, with the addition of horizontal lines to create shadows on the volumes. Shadow determined the form of volumes, then they became a clear composition in the space, Eliminating chaos. These lines seem like spirits to Po Sheng Chen, because they represent the soul of Architecture, but they do not have a specific form or meaning...they are between existing and unexisting! Tezumie is a creative generative artist. He saw the latest experimental drawings of Po Sheng Chen, and after reaching out, the collab was formed with the goal of creating a digital representation of the original concept surrounded by a natural and overgrown environment. The combination of nature and architecture.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: tratti #149
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

metadata.name: BETWEEN #99
metadata.description:
Between thought and embodiment.
A color that is not perceived by the human eye - is a radio wave. 
A structure that we cannot yet see, but it already exists - is a building project. 
Information that continues, despite the fact that there is a pause in the ether - is intuition. 
The BETWEEN project is about subtle worlds that are invisible, but always nearby.

This collection has been created with P5.js.
February 2023.
Press 'S' to save a 3375x4725 PNG file.

metadata.name: Life has no scores #133
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop “Nothing comes from nothing”. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press ‘2’ to save png.
